registers.description:
AVX3 (Advanced_Vector_Extensions) is an earlier name for AVX512 technology. Fuse when set disables all AVX3 (AVX512) instructions (they will report #UD); disables setting AVX512 XFeatureEnabledMask (XCR0[7:5]); Disables reporting of the following CPUID bits:
|| SKL                    || AVX512F, AVX512BW, AVX512DQ, AVX512VL, AVX512CD;
|| CNL and later || AVX512_VBMI, AVX512_IFMA;
|| CLX and later  || AVX512_VNNI; 
|| ICL and later   || AVX512_VPOPCNTDQ, AVX512_VBMI2, AVX512_BITALG, VPCLMULQDQ, VAES*, GFNI* (*evex versions);
|| CPX and later  || AVX512_BF16;
|| WLC and later || AVX512_VP2INTERSECT;
|| GLC and later  || AVX512_FP16.

